@startuml
title Docs frontend — Diagram lightbox open / close sequence

autonumber
hide footbox

actor "Reader" as Reader
participant "img.diagram--uml" as Img
participant "wrapper\n.diagram-uml-wrap" as Wrap
participant "Expand button" as Btn
participant "Lightbox runtime\ndocs-diagram-lightbox.js" as Run
participant "Lightbox surface\n.docs-diagram-lightbox*" as LB
participant "document.body" as Body

== bootstrap (once per page load) ==
Run -> LB : createLightbox()\nappend to body
Run -> Img : scan all img.diagram--uml
Run -> Wrap : wrap each img\n+ append Expand button

== open flow ==
Reader -> Btn : click (or Enter / Space)
Btn -> Run : open(targetImg)
Run -> Run : remember previous focus
Run -> LB : copy src and alt from target
Run -> LB : reset zoom = 1, pan = (0, 0)
Run -> Body : add body lock class
Run -> LB : focus close button

== zoom and pan ==
Reader -> LB : wheel / + / - / Cmd+0 / drag
LB -> Run : delta + position
Run -> Run : clamp scale to [MIN_SCALE, MAX_SCALE]
Run -> LB : apply CSS transform on stage

== close flow ==
Reader -> LB : Escape, click on backdrop, or close button
LB -> Run : close()
Run -> LB : clear src and alt
Run -> Body : remove body lock class
Run -> Btn : restore focus to previous element

note right of Run
  Bootstrap is idempotent: pages without
  img.diagram--uml are no-ops.
  Expand button is appended only once
  per image; duplicate runs are guarded.
end note

@enduml
